Loose and qualifying criteria
In the Czech Republic, the division of construction measures into partial or partial contracts is not mandatory.
An examination of the three major sections of the construction of a motorway ring showed that, if selected parts were allocated on the spot, savings of up to €31.6 million would have been possible, with a total cost of €620.3 million.
