Two thirds of the funds raised for road projects in 2008 and 2009 (i.e. 2.5 billion Euros out of a total of 3.7 billion Euros) were allocated by a total of five companies that carried out the contracts alone or as a working group.
In 46 tendering procedures with an order volume of 528 million euros, only two bidders, or even only one bidder, made an offer.
The NICU showed that a reduction in the market potential could lead to significant cost increases.
