Advance Information and Notice
In the case of construction projects with construction services to be awarded throughout Europe, the public builder must inform interested companies of the planned contracts in advance of the tender.
Preliminary information and announcements form an important basis for Europe-wide competition.
Requirements of EU law and the prevention of corruption
The preliminary information should contain the essential information on the planned construction projects in accordance with public procurement law.
They are required for construction projects where the estimated total contract value exceeds or exceeds the EU threshold and where the client wants to shorten the offer periods of open or non-open procedures.
In notices, the client must provide details of the planned construction contracts to be awarded throughout Europe.
