Bid phase
With the announcement of the award or the invitation to tender, the tender phase begins, in which the companies can make bids on the basis of the tendering documents sent to them.
Applicants can submit their bids until the tender period set by the awarding authority expires.
Requirements of EU law and the prevention of corruption
There are no separate EU legal requirements for this phase of the tendering procedure.
The awarding bodies have to observe the national regulations, which are intended to counteract the possibilities of manipulation existing during the bid phase.
