In some cases, companies awarded contracts at EU-wide contracts even before the expiration of the information periods, which may result in the contract being ineffective.
According to open procedures, contract letters also contained different content in individual cases, such as amended deadlines.
In several cases, the clients did not meet the surcharge deadlines.
In an open procedure, a tendering authority therefore awarded the contract for the second-cheapest offer, since a company with a 50% cheaper offer was no longer willing to perform the services at the originally offered price after the end of the surcharge period.
